    {
        // ── Overview (Article) ───────────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Employees Overview",
            Slug = "employees-overview",
            Summary = "What the Employees module is, the roster and profile views, the detail tabs, and how roles and work location connect to the rest of the system.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 1,
            AppRoutes = """["/employees"]""",
            Tags = """["employees","hr","people"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Employees Overview\n\nThe Employees module is your people directory and HR hub. Managers and Admins get a searchable list of everyone on the team, plus a full profile for each person that brings their employment details, contact info, time, pay, training, compliance, jobs, events, expenses, documents, and change history together in one place.\n\n### Who Can Open It\n\nOnly **Managers** and **Admins** can open Employees. Profiles are view-only here — you look people up and review their records, but you don't add or edit them on this page.\n\n### Adding Employees\n\nYou don't add new employees here. The **Invite Employee** button, which Admins see, takes you to **Admin > Users**, where accounts are created and their basics (role, work location, and so on) are set. Those people then show up here as profiles.\n\n### The List\n\nThe main page shows everyone with their name (Last, First), role, team, job title, email, phone, status, and start date. Use the bar at the top to search by name, email, or phone, and to filter by role or status (Active, Inactive, or All). Click any row to open that person's profile.\n\n### The Profile\n\nClicking a person opens their profile. The top shows their name, role, and whether they're active, plus quick contact links. Just below are five summary cards — Hours this period, Compliance %, Active Jobs, Training %, and Pending Expenses — and each one opens its matching tab.\n\nThe profile has ten tabs:\n- **Overview** — employment details, contact info, address, emergency contact, and clock-in setup (PIN, badge, barcode)\n- **Time** — clocked time for a period you choose (this week, the pay period, or this month)\n- **Pay** — pay stubs showing gross pay, deductions, taxes, and net pay\n- **Training** — training progress and quiz scores\n- **Compliance** — compliance forms and whether they're signed or still pending\n- **Jobs** — the active jobs they're assigned (click one to open it on the board)\n- **Events** — upcoming events and whether they've RSVP'd\n- **Expenses** — their expenses and where each one stands\n- **Documents** — a place to store their files\n- **Activity** — a time-ordered record of changes\n\nThe tab you're on shows in the web address, so you can bookmark or share a specific view.\n\n### Roles and Work Location\n\n**Role** comes from your organization's list of roles and sets what the person can do across the app. It shows as a label at the top of their profile, and you can filter the list by it.\n\n**Work Location** is the company location the person works from, and it matters for HR and taxes — it sets which state's withholding and rules apply to them. You'll find it under Employment Details on the Overview tab.\n\n### Clock-In Setup\n\nThe Overview tab's clock-in section shows whether the person is set up to clock in on the shop floor: a PIN, a badge they can tap, and a barcode they can scan. These let them clock in and sign in at shop-floor screens.\n\n### When to Use Employees\n\n- To look up a coworker's role, team, contact info, or work location\n- To review someone's time, pay, training, or compliance in one place\n- To check which jobs a person is assigned\n- To upload or review someone's documents\n- To see a record of changes to a person's information","sections":[]}"""
        });

