value":"How much of their compliance is done. Click to open the Compliance tab."},{"label":"Active Jobs","value":"How many active jobs they're assigned. Click to open the Jobs tab."},{"label":"Training %","value":"How far along their training is. Click to open the Training tab."},{"label":"Pending Expenses","value":"How many expenses are still open. Click to open the Expenses tab."}]},{"heading":"Overview Tab — Employment Details","items":[{"label":"Role","value":"The person's role, which sets what they can do in the app. Always shown."},{"label":"Job Title","value":"Their job title. Optional."},{"label":"Department","value":"Their department. Optional."},{"label":"Team","value":"Their team. Optional."},{"label":"Work Location","value":"The company location they work from. It sets which state's tax rules and withholding apply. Optional — the company's main location is used if left blank."},{"label":"Start Date","value":"The date they were hired. Optional."},{"label":"Status","value":"An Active or Inactive label."}]},{"heading":"Overview Tab — Contact, Address, Emergency, System Access","items":[{"label":"Work Email","value":"Their main work email, shown as a link. Always shown."},{"label":"Personal Email","value":"A backup contact email. Optional."},{"label":"Phone","value":"Their phone number, shown as a link. Optional."},{"label":"Address","value":"Street, city, state, and ZIP. Shows only when a street address is on file."},{"label":"Emergency Contact","value":"Name, relationship, and phone. Shows only when an emergency contact is on file."},{"label":"PIN Configured","value":"Whether a clock-in PIN is set up. Yes or No."},{"label":"RFID / NFC","value":"Whether a badge they can tap to clock in is set up."},{"label":"Barcode","value":"Whether a barcode they can scan to clock in is set up."},{"label":"Compliance counter","value":"How many compliance items are done out of the total, for example 3 of 5."}]},{"heading":"Profile Tabs","items":[{"label":"Overview","value":"Their employment details, contact info, address, emergency contact, and clock-in setup."},{"label":"Time","value":"Their clocked time for a period you choose — this week, the pay period, or this month — with the date, length, category, job, and notes for each entry."},{"label":"Pay","value":"Their pay stubs, showing the pay date, period, gross pay, deductions, taxes, and net pay."},{"label":"Training","value":"Their training, showing each module's type, status, score, and start and finish dates."},{"label":"Compliance","value":"Their compliance forms, showing each form's type, status, and signed and created dates."},{"label":"Jobs","value":"The active jobs they're assigned, with number, title, stage, priority, and due date. Click a row to open the job on the board."},{"label":"Events","value":"Their upcoming events, with the type, start and end times, location, whether it's required, and their RSVP."},{"label":"Expenses","value":"Their expenses, with the date, category, description, amount, and status."},{"label":"Documents","value":"A drop zone for their files. Accepts PDF, Word, and image files up to 25MB each."},{"label":"Activity","value":"A time-ordered record of changes to this person's information."}]},{"heading":"Statuses and Labels","items":[{"label":"Employment status","value":"Active shows a green label, Inactive a gray one."},{"label":"Training status","value":"Not started (gray), in progress (blue), completed (green), or failed (red)."},{"label":"Compliance status","value":"Pending (yellow), signed or completed (green), or expired (red)."},{"label":"Expense status","value":"Pending (yellow), approved (green), rejected (red), or reimbursed (blue)."},{"label":"Event RSVP","value":"Invited (blue), accepted (green), or declined (red)."}]},{"heading":"Access and Connections","items":[{"label":"Who can open it","value":"Only Managers and Admins. Profiles are view-only on this page."},{"label":"Adding or editing people","value":"Done in Admin > Users, reached from the Invite Employee button (Admins only)."},{"label":"Role","value":"Sets what the person can do across the app. Shown as a label and used to filter the list."},{"label":"Work Location","value":"The company location they work from. It sets which state's tax rules and withholding apply."}]}]}"""
        });

        // ── Knowledge Check (Quiz) ───────────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Employees Knowledge Check",
            Slug = "employees-quiz",
            Summary = "Test your knowledge of the Employees module: access, the roster, profile tabs, roles, work location, and system access.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Quiz,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 4,
            AppRoutes = """["/employees"]""",
            Tags = """["employees","hr","people","quiz"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"passingScore":80,"questionsPerQuiz":8,"shuffleOptions":true,"showExplanationsAfterSubmit":true,"questions":[{"id":"em1","text":"Who can open the Employees module?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Everyone who's logged in"},{"id":"b","text":"Only Admins and Managers","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Only the employee looking at their own record"},{"id":"d","text":"Anyone with a shop-floor PIN"}],"explanation":"Only Admins and Managers can open Employees. Other people can't, and even Admins and Managers only view profiles here — they can't edit them on this page."},{"id":"em2","text":"How do you add a new employee?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Click 'New Employee' on the list and fill out a form"},{"id":"b","text":"Use the Invite Employee button, which takes you to Admin > Users where accounts are created","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Right-click the list and choose 'Add'"},{"id":"d","text":"Employees are added automatically from their clocked time"}],"explanation":"You don't add employees here. The Invite Employee button, which Admins see, opens Admin > Users, where the account and its basics are set up. The new person then shows up here as a profile."},{"id":"em3","text":"In the list, how is an employee's name shown?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"First Last (for example, Daniel Hartman)"},{"id":"b","text":"Last, First (for example, Hartman, Daniel)","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Username only"},{"id":"d","text":"Email address"}],"explanation":"Names are shown Last, First throughout the app — so the list and profile show 'Hartman, Daniel' rather than 'Daniel Hartman'."},{"id":"em4","text":"Why does an employee's Work Location matter?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It sets the color of their name label"},{"id":"b","text":"It sets which state's withholding and rules apply","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"It controls which board they appear on"},{"id":"d","text":"It sets their pay rate"}],"explanation":"Work Location is the company location the person works from. It sets which state's withholding and tax rules apply to them, and you'll find it under Employment Details on the Overview tab."},{"id":"em5","text":"You want to see an employee's pay stubs with gross pay, taxes, and net pay. Which tab do you open?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Time"},{"id":"b","text":"Pay","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Compliance"},{"id":"d","text":"Activity"}],"explanation":"The Pay tab lists pay stubs showing the pay date, period, gross pay, deductions, taxes, and net pay. The Time tab is for clocked time, not pay."},{"id":"em6","text":"What happens when you click one of the five summary cards on a profile (for example, Active Jobs)?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It opens a printable report"},{"id":"b","text":"It opens the matching tab (for example, the Jobs tab)","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"It lets you edit that number right there"},{"id":"d","text":"It reloads the whole page"}],"explanation":"Each summary card opens its matching tab — Hours opens Time, Compliance % opens Compliance, Active Jobs opens Jobs, Training % opens Training, and Pending Expenses opens Expenses."},{"id":"em7","text":"Where do you filter the list by a role, and where do the role choices come from?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The Role filter in the filter bar; the choices come from your organization's roles","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"The Role filter; the choices are a fixed built-in list"},{"id":"c","text":"There is no role filter — you have to search by name"},{"id":"d","text":"Only in Admin > Users"}],"explanation":"The filter bar has a Role menu, and its choices come from your organization's own roles rather than a fixed list. Pick a role to narrow the list."},{"id":"em8","text":"What does the clock-in setup on the Overview tab tell you about an employee?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Their salary and benefits"},{"id":"b","text":"Whether they have a PIN, a tap badge, and a barcode set up","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Which managers can approve their time"},{"id":"d","text":"When they last logged in"}],"explanation":"The clock-in section shows what the person is set up to use on the shop floor: a PIN, a badge they can tap, and a barcode they can scan, plus a count of their compliance items."},{"id":"em9","text":"How many tabs does the employee profile have, and which one opens first?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Five tabs, opening on Pay"},{"id":"b","text":"Ten tabs, opening on Overview","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Three tabs, opening on Activity"},{"id":"d","text":"Ten tabs, opening on Documents"}],"explanation":"The profile has ten tabs — Overview, Time, Pay, Training, Compliance, Jobs, Events, Expenses, Documents, and Activity — and opens on Overview."},{"id":"em10","text":"On the Jobs tab, what happens when you click a job row?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It removes the job assignment"},{"id":"b","text":"It opens the job on the board","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"It marks the job complete"},{"id":"d","text":"It saves the job as a PDF"}],"explanation":"The Jobs tab lists the person's active jobs. Clicking a row opens that job on the board so you can see it in context."},{"id":"em11","text":"What file types and size does the Documents tab accept?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Only PDFs, up to 5MB"},{"id":"b","text":"PDF, Word, and images, up to 25MB each","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Any file type, with no size limit"},{"id":"d","text":"Only images, up to 25MB"}],"explanation":"The Documents tab is a drop zone that accepts PDF, Word, and image files, up to 25MB each."},{"id":"em12","text":"In the list, a column shows a dash instead of a value (for example, under Team or Phone). What does that mean?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The information is still loading and will show up soon"},{"id":"b","text":"That optional field was left blank for this person","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The field is hidden from you"},{"id":"d","text":"The employee is inactive"}],"explanation":"Optional fields like Team, Job Title, and Phone show a dash when they're empty. It just means nothing was entered there — not that it's hidden or still loading."}]}"""
